    private void initComponents() {

        jScrollPane1 = new javax.swing.JScrollPane();
        jEditorPane1 = new javax.swing.JEditorPane();

        setDefaultCloseOperation(javax.swing.WindowConstants.DISPOSE_ON_CLOSE);

        jEditorPane1.setContentType("text/html");
        jEditorPane1.setEditable(false);
        jEditorPane1.setText("<html xmlns:v=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:vml\"\nxmlns:o=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office\"\nxmlns:w=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word\"\nxmlns:m=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/2004/12/omml\"\nxmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40\">\n\n\n\n<body lang=EN-US style='tab-interval:.5in'>\n\n<div class=Section1>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:center;\nline-height:150%'><b><span style='font-size:15.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>Description of <span class=SpellE>F~CompSynth</span>: A Matching and\nSynthesis Toolkit</span></b></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>A\ntoolkit, <span class=SpellE>F~CompSynth</span>, has been developed where the\nalgorithms and data structures mentioned earlier are implemented such as it can\nbe used in industry. The name <span class=SpellE>F~CompSynth</span> stands for\n\u201cFast and Dynamic Component Synthesizer\u201d. The toolkit has been developed using\nJava6 platform (<span class=SpellE>jdk</span> 1.6). Java is chosen because of\nits cross platform execution facilities. In general, OS platform of most of the\nVLSI CAD software is Windows and Linux. <span class=SpellE>F~CompSynth</span>\nis a supporting toolkit. Therefore, a single version of the toolkit is enough\nto execute on both the platform. As a result, a \u201cjar\u201d file is produced that can\nbe distribute as the desktop application as well as web application. </span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>The\nentire implementation can be considered as a composition of an Interactive\nLayout Editor and a Matching Wizard. In this section, the features with some\nscreenshots of <span class=SpellE>F~CompSynth</span>&nbsp;is discussed in\ndetails below. </span></p>\n\n<h4 style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:\n.75in;text-indent:-.5in;line-height:150%;page-break-after:avoid'><b><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";letter-spacing:-.1pt'>1.1.</span></b><b><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";letter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></b><b><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Interactive\nLayout Editor</span></b><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\"'><o:p></o:p></span></h4>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>The\nauxiliary but very important part of the thesis is the development of\nInteractive Layout Editor. This is the platform for automatic as well as manual\nlayout editing. </span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Its\nmain graphical user interface is consists of five components. A screenshot with\nmarking of the components is given at Figure 26. Descriptions of the components\nare given below. At the specified figure the components are labeled with\nalphabetic symbols. The functionalities of the tools are kept as minimal as\npossible to facilitate user learning. For industrial needs they can be\nexpanded. </span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;\nmargin-left:.85in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5in;line-height:150%'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>1.1.1.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Editing Canvas</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>The\nediting canvas is the place where the rectangles of devices are visualized. It\nis possible to add rectangles, resize and delete them. Addition of rectangle is\ndone by drawing it using mouse. At resizing, the border will be highlighted and\ndragging the border will cause the change of its size. The entire canvas can be\nzoomed in and out. At a certain level of zoom, the canvas is divided by grids.\nDrawing is bound to the grids. Generally, one grid call represents 0.1 micron. </span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;\nmargin-left:.85in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5in;line-height:150%'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>1.1.2.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Menus</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Menus\nare the main command area. There are five main menus. The menus with their menu\nitems are listed along with a short description.</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>a)</span><span style='font-size:\n7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>File</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:\n-.25in'><span class=GramE><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>a</span></span><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>.</span><span style='font-size:\n7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>New: Clearing all\nthe components</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:\n-.25in'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>b.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>Add Device: Add a device from a DTS&nbsp;file</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:\n-.25in'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>c.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>Save: Save the current layout information in a text file</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:\n-.25in'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>d.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>Save <span class=GramE>As</span> GDSII: Save the current\nlayout information in a GDSII file</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:\n-.25in'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>e.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>Exit: Closing the application</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>b)</span><span style='font-size:\n7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Options</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:\n-.25in'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>a.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>Fill Rectangles: Toggle between transparent and filled\nvisualization of the rectangles</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:\n-.25in'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>b.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>Show Grid: Toggle between showing and not the grid </span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:\n-.25in'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>c.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>Scaling Factor: Set 1 grid unit = x micron</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>c)</span><span style='font-size:\n7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Tools</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:\n-.25in'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>a.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>Matching Wizard: The wizard to synthesis matched components.</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:\n-.25in'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>b.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>Read GDSII: <span class=GramE>A test tool which parse</span>\na GDSII file and translated it into text format</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:\n-.25in'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>c.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>Go To: Go to specified coordinate</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>d)</span><span style='font-size:\n7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Component</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:\n-.25in'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>a.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>New Component: Add a new empty component </span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:\n-.25in'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>b.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>Move Component: Move the specified component to a\nspecified location</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:\n-.25in'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>c.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>Show Component: Move to the coordinate of the specified\ncomponent to bring it in the visible area</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:\n-.25in'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>d.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>Component List: Show the list of rectangles of the\ncomponents and layers</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>e)</span><span style='font-size:\n7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Help</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:\n-.25in'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>a.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>Help: Show a quick help</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:\n-.25in'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>b.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>About: Show the development information of the tool</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";letter-spacing:\n-.1pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;\nmargin-left:.85in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5in;line-height:150%'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>1.1.3.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Layer Tool</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Layer\ntool contains the list of the mask layers. The layers can be loaded dynamically\nfrom a layer database or data file. Before drawing a rectangle, it is necessary\nto select the specific layer. The color shown as background of the layer label\nis also used as the color of the rectangle of that layer. A visibility option\nof the layer is attached with the layers. With the unselect of the visibility\nof a layer, all the rectangles of that layer will be invisible. </span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;\nmargin-left:.85in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5in;line-height:150%'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>1.1.4.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Toolbar</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Only\nquick action modes are given at the toolbar. The default action mode is \u2018Draw\u2019.\nMoreover, \u2018Edit\u2019, \u2018Delete\u2019, \u2018Zoom In\u2019 and \u2018Zoom Out\u2019 are also placed on the\ntoolbar. To resize a rectangle, it is necessary to select the \u2018Edit\u2019 mode.\nSelection of \u2018Delete\u2019 will cause deletion with a click on a rectangle\u2019s\ntop-left corner. \u2018Zoom In\u2019 and \u2018Zoom Out\u2019 should be selected to zoom in or out\nan area.&nbsp; </span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;\nmargin-left:.85in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5in;line-height:150%'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>1.1.5.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Component List</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Component\nList contains the entire currently loaded components. A component can be\nselected as the \u2018Current Component\u2019 by double clicking on it. To delete a\ncomponent a component should be selected and it should be followed by the\n\u2018Delete\u2019 key press.&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:13.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<h4 style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:\n.75in;text-indent:-.5in;line-height:150%;page-break-after:avoid'><b><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";letter-spacing:-.1pt'>1.2.</span></b><b><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";letter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></b><b><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Matching Wizard</span></b><span\nstyle='mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\"'><o:p></o:p></span></h4>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>The\nprinciple implementation of the thesis is the Matching Wizard. It is a four\nstep wizard that is designed to be used in a very flexible way. All the\nalgorithms stated above are implemented in this part. The main purpose of the\ntool is to synthesis the components so that they match themselves in an\nappropriate way. </span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>With\nillustration the steps are discussed below.</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;\nmargin-left:.85in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5in;line-height:150%'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>1.2.1.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;</span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:\n150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Component</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:6.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>First\nstep of Matching Wizard is to collect the basic information of the component. At\nfirst number of total components must be mentioned. Dummy should be considered\nas also a component. This is followed by the selection of the DTS&nbsp;file of\nthe device or component. </span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:13.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>\u2018Browse\u2019\nbutton facilitates browsing the computer file system and selection of the file.\nNext user has to put the unit size (L for length and W for width) of the\ncomponent part. The length and width can be double precision floating number\nand measured in micron. \u2018Next\u2019 button always forward the wizard steps.</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;\nmargin-left:.85in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5in;line-height:150%'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>1.2.2.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;</span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:\n150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Component Parts</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>At\nthe second step, all of the component name which will be appeared as part label\nalso should be entered. It is followed by entering the number of parts or\n\u2018Multiple\u2019 of the components. \u2018Previous\u2019 button causes reappearance of the\nprevious step.</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:13.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;\nmargin-left:.85in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5in;line-height:150%'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>1.2.3.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Matching\nSimulator</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>The\nmost principal and challenging area of the thesis is the implementation of\nMatching Simulator. Here the matching models are implemented and an interactive\nmodel simulator is provided. The entire simulator can be divided horizontally\nin two parts. At right the placement matrix is shown. This is a very compact\narrangement of the simulation tools.</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:13.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;\nmargin-left:1.2in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.75in;line-height:150%'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>1.2.3.1.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Matrix\nSize</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>The\n\u2018Matrix\u2019 labeled combo box enlists the possible matrix sizes for the\narrangements. This is calculated from the factors of the total number of the\nparts.&nbsp; Every time the numbers of parts are changed, the items are also\nchanged in the combo box.</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;\nmargin-left:1.2in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.75in;line-height:150%'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>1.2.3.2.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Matching\nModel</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>The\n\u2018Matching Model\u2019 labeled combo box contains the implemented \u2018Matching Models\u2019.\nSome models are variation of others. The following four labels are some\nmeasurement of the matching of the parts. Last of them indicates the total\nweight or point of the arrangement. The less point indicates better matching. </span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;\nmargin-left:1.2in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.75in;line-height:150%'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>1.2.3.3.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Customize</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>At\nthe customize tool, the components\u2019 name and their multiples (number of parts)\nare shown and it is possible to change the multiples as necessity. It is often\nnecessary for dummy component. Changing of number of component requires going\nto the first step. </span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;\nmargin-left:1.2in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.75in;line-height:150%'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>1.2.3.4.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Commands</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>\u2018Re\nCalculate\u2019 button adopts the changes of matrix size, matching model and\ncomponent multiples and rearranges the placement matrix. \u2018Suggest\u2019 button\nsuggests the best model based on the point calculation.</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;\nmargin-left:1.2in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.75in;line-height:150%'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>1.2.3.5.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Placement&nbsp;Matrix</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>At\nthe right, the placement matrix is visualized where the cells contain the\nrepresentation of the parts of the components. Each parts of a component are\nindicated with the same colored rectangle cells. On the other hand, parts of\nthe different components are represented by different colors.</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;\nmargin-left:1.2in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.75in;line-height:150%'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>1.2.3.6.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Interactivity\n</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>The\nplacement matrix is an interactive tool. It has brought a great flexibility in\ndesign of component matching that accelerates user choice fully. The\narrangement can be changed manually by drag and drop fashion. </span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Dragging\na part of a component and dropping on a part of different component will cause\na swap action between the parts. </span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>\u2018Right\nClick\u2019 on a part will cause changing its membership to other component (the\nnext component). The part of last component can be changed to the first\ncomponent in circular rotation fashion. At each arrangement, the point will be\nrecalculated. </span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;\nmargin-left:.85in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5in;line-height:150%'><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>1.2.4.</span><span\nstyle='font-size:7.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span\nstyle='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>Layout Info</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>In\nthis step, two parameters, horizontal distance and vertical distance are\nreceived. The parameters may be manual or automatic. Automaticity is done by\naddition of the variables listed in the DRS file and DTS&nbsp;file. Selecting a\nvariable item and clicking on \u2018Add\u2019 will build an expression of addition of current\nvariable with the previous expression. A negative checkbox is provided to\nnegate the entire expression. At the right of the expression textbox the\nevaluated value is shown. At last the \u2018Finish\u2019 clicking will cause final\nsynthesis and physical placement of the components.</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:13.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\nletter-spacing:-.1pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\n150%'><span style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:150%;letter-spacing:-.1pt'>At\nthe end of the wizard, the physical devices are visualized on the canvas\neliminating all previous components. </span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal>&nbsp;</p>\n\n</div>\n\n</body>\n\n</html>\n");
        jScrollPane1.setViewportView(jEditorPane1);

        getContentPane().add(jScrollPane1, java.awt.BorderLayout.CENTER);

        java.awt.Dimension screenSize = java.awt.Toolkit.getDefaultToolkit().getScreenSize();
        setBounds((screenSize.width-800)/2, (screenSize.height-550)/2, 800, 550);
    }// </editor-fold>//GEN-END:initComponents
    
